Inquest on Anya Shahin's Death
1986-7-4

Office of the Judge Advocate General
Report of Investigation on the dead body of Anya Shahin held on July 4, 1986.

Date of Individual’s Death: July 2, 1986

Apparent Cause of Death: gunshot wounds to the head, torso and arms

Suspected Weapon (if any): M14 rifle, 7.62x51mm NATO cartriges

Results of Medical Examination: [because the body was not retrieved after the
firefight], no medical examination was requested

Circumstances Surrounding Individual’s Death: [individual fired upon and killed
Major Calvin Grubbs, resulting in a brief firefight with U.S. Army soldiers,
resulting in the individual’s fatal injuries]